 communities that later demanded their return. Some Native people collected for museums and even created their own.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIroquoian IndiansxAntiquitiesxCollection and preservationzOntario. 0aIroquoian IndiansxMaterial culturexStudy and teachingzOntario. 0aOjibwa IndiansxAntiquitiesxCollection and preservationzOntario. 0aOjibwa IndiansxMaterial culturexStudy and teachingzOntario. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010z978311127414008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010z978311127721940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077358065740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773580657423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773580657/original  a978-3-11-127414-0  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010c2010d2011  a978-3-11-127721-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010c2010d2011  aGBV-deGruyter-alles